quran[33]{c,v,t}:
  43,24,"[The warner] said, “Even if I bring you a better guidance than what you have found your forefathers upon?” They said, “We totally reject what you [prophets] have been sent with.”"
  43,25,So We took revenge from them; see what was the end of the deniers
  43,26,"And [remember] when Abraham said to his father and his people, “I disown all that you worship"
  43,27,except the One Who created me; He will surely guide me.”
  43,28,"And he made it a lasting word among his descendants, so that they may return [to Allah]"
  43,29,"However, I let these [Makkans] and their forefathers enjoy their lives, until there came to them the truth and a clear messenger"
  43,30,"But when the truth came to them, they said, “This is magic, and we definitely reject it.”"
  43,31,"And they said, “Why was this Qur’an not sent down to a great man from one of the two towns?”"
  43,32,"Is it they who distribute the mercy of your Lord? It is We Who have distributed their livelihood among them in the life of this world, and have raised some of them above others in ranks, so that they may serve one another. But the mercy of your Lord is better than what they accumulate"
  43,33,"Were it not that all people might become a single community [of disbelievers], We would have given those who disbelieve in the Most Compassionate houses of sliver roofs and staircases to ascend"
  43,34,"and their houses having [silver] doors and couches on which they recline"
  43,35,"and [golden] ornaments. But all of these are mere enjoyments of the life of this world, and the Hereafter with your Lord is [only] for those who fear Allah"
  43,36,"Whoever turns away from the Reminder of the Most Compassionate [the Qur’an], We assign to him a devil to be his close associate"
  43,37,"who will surely avert them from the [right] way, while they think that they are rightly guided"
  43,38,"Then when he comes to Us, he will say [to his devil associate], “I wish you were as distant from me as the east and west. What a terrible associate [you were]!”"
  43,39,"[They will be told], “As you have done wrong, it will not benefit you Today that you are sharing the punishment.”"
  43,40,"Can you make the deaf hear, or guide the blind or the one who is clearly misguided"
  43,41,"Either We take you away [in death], We will surely exact retribution upon them"
  43,42,"or We will show you what We warned them of, for We have full power over them"
  43,43,So hold fast to what is revealed to you. You are indeed on a straight path
  43,44,"Indeed, this [Qur’an] is a reminder for you and your people, and surely you will [all] be questioned"
  43,45,"Ask those of Our messengers whom We sent before you: Did We appoint gods to be worshiped besides the Most Compassionate"
  43,46,"Indeed, We sent Moses with Our signs to Pharaoh and his courtiers, so he said: “I am a messenger of the Lord of the worlds.”"
  43,47,"But as soon as he came to them with Our signs, they laughed at them"
  43,48,"Every sign We showed them was greater than the one before it, and We seized them with punishment so that they may turn in repentance"
  43,49,"They said, “O magician, call upon your Lord for us, by virtue of the covenant He has made with you; we will surely accept guidance.”"
  43,50,"But as soon We removed the punishment from them, they broke their promise"
  43,51,"Pharaoh proclaimed to his people, “O my people, does not the kingdom of Egypt belong to me, and these streams flowing at my feet? Do you not see"
  43,52,Or am I not better than this contemptible one who can hardly express himself
  43,53,Then why there are not sent down upon him bracelets of gold or come with him angels to support him?”
  43,54,Thus he made fool of his people and they obeyed him. They were indeed a wicked people
  43,55,"When they angered Us, We exacted Our retribution and drowned them all"
  43,56,Thus We made them a precedent and an example for the later generations